# Choose Fulfillment Store

> Boundary: `choose_fulfillment_store(items: object, constraints: object) -> object`

## Purpose

Pick the store that can most reliably fulfill an order.

## Behavior

Each candidate has `id`, `cost`, `value`, `risk_penalty`, and `delay_penalty`.
Cost is drive minutes. Value is how much of the requested cart the store can
fulfill. Risk penalty represents low-stock risk. Delay penalty represents
courier congestion.

Select the candidate set with the highest score while total cost is no more
than `constraints.max_cost`. For this chapter, each store candidate is given a
cost equal to the max cost, so the selected set is exactly one store. When
`constraints.risk` is at least 7, subtract risk penalties. When
`constraints.delay` is at least 6, subtract delay penalties.

Return selected store ids, total cost, score, and warnings.

## Examples

### Nearby store wins when it can fill the cart

Input `items`:
```json
[
  {"id": "north-market", "cost": 12, "value": 96, "risk_penalty": 4, "delay_penalty": 3},
  {"id": "west-market", "cost": 12, "value": 82, "risk_penalty": 1, "delay_penalty": 2},
  {"id": "hub-store", "cost": 12, "value": 90, "risk_penalty": 2, "delay_penalty": 8}
]
```

Input `constraints`:
```json
{"max_cost": 12, "risk": 3, "delay": 2}
```

Returns:
```json
{"selected_ids": ["north-market"], "total_cost": 12, "score": 96, "warnings": []}
```

### High congestion avoids the hub

Input `items`:
```json
[
  {"id": "north-market", "cost": 12, "value": 88, "risk_penalty": 4, "delay_penalty": 2},
  {"id": "west-market", "cost": 12, "value": 86, "risk_penalty": 1, "delay_penalty": 1},
  {"id": "hub-store", "cost": 12, "value": 91, "risk_penalty": 2, "delay_penalty": 12}
]
```

Input `constraints`:
```json
{"max_cost": 12, "risk": 3, "delay": 8}
```

Returns:
```json
{"selected_ids": ["north-market"], "total_cost": 12, "score": 86, "warnings": ["delay penalties applied"]}
```
